SIMPLE: intrapetiolar
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Intrapetiolar
<hw>In`tra*pet"i*o*lar</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>Situated between the petiole and the stem; --
said of the pair of stipules at the base of a petiole when united by
those margins next the petiole, thus seeming to form a single stipule
between the petiole and the stem or branch; -- often confounded with
<xex>interpetiolar</xex>, from which it differs essentially in
meaning.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Intraterritorial</ent>⟦br⟧
